<dl id="n08055i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08055i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08055i"> 55(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> lifts up bimbi</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans mon enfance, j&apos;ai connu deux fr&egrave;res, l&apos;un, sorte de g&eacute;ant, ressemblait &agrave; un hercule de foire ; son &eacute;criture &eacute;tait grande et &eacute;paisse; l&apos;autre, maigre, &agrave; l&apos;aspect souffreteux, avait une &eacute;criture tr&egrave;s fine et l&eacute;g&egrave;re. Le premier me terrifiait parce qu&apos;il avait la manie de m&apos;enlever &agrave; bout de bras, pour montrer sa force, et j&apos;&eacute;tais peu rassur&eacute; pendant ses exercices. Il se plaisait &agrave; narguer son fr&egrave;re, en se livrant &agrave; des abus de toutes sortes, buvant et mangeant avec exc&egrave;s, apparemment infatigable au travail comme au plaisir. Il est mort d&apos;une congestion c&eacute;r&eacute;brale &agrave; 42 ans. Le second dirigeait sa vie tr&egrave;s prudemment, bornant ses ambitions, se contentant d&apos;une activit&eacute; restreinte. A 16 ans, on l&apos;avait retir&eacute; du coll&egrave;ge parce que les &eacute;tudes le fatiguaient ; cepen dant il n&apos;a fait aucune maladie grave au cours de sa vie, quoiqu&apos;il se soign&acirc;t toujours comme s&apos;il &eacute;tait en convalescence. Il est mort &agrave; 74 ans. En voyant les deux fr&egrave;res si diff&eacute;rents, personne n&apos;aurait os&eacute; pronostiquer un tel avenir. <br><font color="green">[n my childhood, I knew two brothers, one, a sort of giant, looked like a fair herculean; his writing was large and thick; the other, lean, with a sickly appearance, had a very fine and light handwriting. The first terrified me because he had the mania to remove me at arm&apos;s length, to show his strength, and I was not reassured during his exercises. He liked to taunt his brother, by indulging in all kinds of abuses, drinking and eating excessively, seemingly unfit for work and pleasure. He died of cerebral congestion at age 42. The second directed his life very cautiously, limiting his ambitions, being content with a restricted activity. At the age of sixteen, he had been taken out of college because studies tired him; However, he has not made any serious illness in his life, although he is always treated as if he were recovering. He died at 74 years old. Seeing the two brothers so different, no one would have dared to predict such a future.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 223</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: It. <i>Bimbi</i>, babies. </mm> </dd></dl>
